ing%20the%20risk%20of%20it%20getting%20damaged.%20But%20they%20survived%2C%20and%20the%20bottom%20of%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20oceans%20began%20to%20become%20overcrowded%20with%20living%20little%20blobs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20297px)%2085vw%2C%20297px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164013%2FThe-Shortest-History-of-Sex-front-cover.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22297%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164013%2FThe-Shortest-History-of-Sex-front-cover.jpg%20782w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164013%2FThe-Shortest-History-of-Sex-front-cover-196x300.jpg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164013%2FThe-Shortest-History-of-Sex-front-cover-667x1024.jpg%20667w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695683%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22456%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Shortest%20History%20of%20Sex%2C%20David%20Baker%2C%20Pan%20Macmillan%20India%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20overcome%20the%20shortage%20of%20%E2%80%98real%20estate%E2%80%99%203.4%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20some%20prokaryotes%20evolved%20to%20live%20near%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20oceans%2C%20no%20longer%20keeping%20themselves%20warm%20with%20underwater%20volcanoes.%20Instead%2C%20these%20new%20microscopic%20blobs%20evolved%20to%20use%20the%20Sun%E2%80%99s%20energy.%20They%20used%20photosynthesis%2C%20converting%20water%2C%20sunlight%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20(CO2)%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20to%20feed%20themselves.%20Just%20like%20plants%20today.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20just%20like%20plants%20today%2C%20they%20pumped%20oxygen%20(O2)%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20as%20a%20waste%20product.%20The%20problem%20is%20that%20oxygen%20is%20highly%20turbulent%2C%20can%20create%20violent%20chemical%20reactions%20and%20in%20large%20quantities%20could%20kill%20fragile%20primitive%20life%20like%20those%20ancestral%20microbes%20that%20had%20evolved%20on%20an%20early%20Earth%20where%20there%20was%20very%20little%20oxygen%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202.5%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20microscopic%20photosynthesisers%20had%20increased%20the%20level%20of%20oxygen%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20from%20next%20to%20nothing%20to%202.5%20per%20cent.%20This%20nasty%20chemical%20killed%20off%20scores%20of%20microbes%20in%20an%20event%20known%20as%20the%20Oxygen%20Holocaust%2C%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20first%20known%20mass%20extinction%20event%20and%20one%20of%20the%20only%20mass%20extinction%20events%20(before%20humans)%20kicked%20off%20by%20living%20organisms%20rather%20than%20an%20asteroid%20impact%20or%20a%20super-volcanic%20eruption.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20surviving%20microbes%20evolved%20an%20increasing%20tolerance%20for%20oxygen%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%20Some%20of%20them%20even%20evolved%20the%20ability%20to%20consume%20oxygen%20instead%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20reversing%20which%20chemical%20was%20food%20and%20which%20waste.%20These%20were%20the%20first%20aerobic%20species%2C%20microscopic%20creatures%20similar%20in%20that%20respect%20to%20humans%20and%20other%20animals.%20We%20inhale%20oxygen%2C%20we%20exhale%20carbon%20dioxide.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20photosynthesisers%20remained%20the%20majority%20of%20living%20things%20on%20Earth%20and%20continued%20to%20create%20unmitigated%20disasters%20by%20pumping%20out%20oxygen.%20Enough%20O2%20had%20gathered%20in%20the%20atmosphere%202.2%20billion%20years%20ago%20that%20the%20oxygen%20atoms%20began%20to%20group%20together%20in%20threes%2C%20creating%20ozone%20(O3).%20The%20resulting%20ozone%20layer%20that%20blanketed%20Earth%20reflected%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20Sun%E2%80%99s%20rays%20back%20into%20space.%20While%20we%20desperately%20require%20the%20ozone%20layer%20to%20protect%20us%20from%20solar%20radiation%20today%2C%20in%20the%20short%20term%202.2%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20this%20was%20not%20a%20good%20thing.%20Photosynthesising%20life%20continued%20to%20increase%20the%20thickness%20of%20the%20ozone%20layer.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Earth%20got%20colder%20and%20colder.%20The%20oceans%20froze%20at%20the%20poles.%20Then%20the%20ice%20spread%20down%20towards%20the%20equator%2C%20encasing%20the%20entire%20planet%20in%20a%20frozen%20prison%2C%20in%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98Snowball%20Earth%E2%80%99%20event%2C%20roughly%202%20billion%20years%20ago.%20The%20average%20global%20temperature%20would%20have%20been%20around%20-50%C2%B0C.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESnowball%20Earth%20imposed%20a%20strain%20on%20the%20microbes%20living%20in%20the%20now%20ice-covered%20oceans.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20the%20strain%2C%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20microbe%20evolved%3A%20the%20eukaryote.%20These%20are%20%E2%80%98beefier%E2%80%99%20cells%2C%2010%20to%201000%20times%20the%20size%20of%20prokaryotes%2C%20which%20also%20evolved%20to%20protect%20their%20DNA%20by%20keeping%20it%20in%20a%20central%20nucleus%20instead%20of%20letting%20the%20strands%20just%20float%20around%20the%20cell.%20We%20humans%20are%20descended%20from%20these%20eukaryotes%2C%20as%20are%20all%20the%20ancestors%20and%20descendants%20in%20the%20evolutionary%20tree%20of%20the%20plant%20and%20animal%20kingdoms.%20And%20it%20is%20these%20tiny%20eukaryotic%20blobs%20that%20were%20the%20first%20creatures%20to%20have%20sex.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20same%20disastrous%20Snowball%20Earth%20period%2C%20these%20microscopic%20eukaryotes%20began%20to%20engage%20in%20carnal%20relations%20with%20one%20another%20%E2%80%93%20as%20does%2099.9%20per%20cent%20of%20all%20eukaryotic%20life%20today.%20The%20habit%20stuck%20and%20has%20grown%20only%20more%20thrilling%20and%20perplexing.%20But%20the%20question%20of%20how%20and%20why%20our%20microbial%20ancestors%20began%20to%20feel%20compelled%20to%20exchange%20genetic%20information%2C%20in%20the%20same%20way%20two%20people%20might%20exchange%20phone%20numbers%20at%20a%20bar%2C%20remains%20shrouded%20in%20mystery.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20above%20is%20an%20excerpt%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Shortest%20History%20of%20Sex%2C%3Cem%3E%20an%20exploration%20of%20sexual%20evolution%2C%20tracing%20it%20from%20approximately%20two%20billion%20years%20ago%20until%20the%20present%20time%2C%20by%20David%20Baker.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDavid%20Baker%20is%20a%20history%20and%20science%20writer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707045382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164413%2FSnowball_Huronian.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-disastrous-origins-of-sex%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20disastrous%20Snowball%20Earth%20period%2C%20microscopic%20eukaryotes%20began%20to%20engage%20in%20carnal%20relations%20with%20one%20another.%20For%20some%20reason%2C%20the%20habit%20stuck.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-disastrous-origins-of-sex%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gill%20Given%20Ultimatum%20Ahead%20Of%20Vizag%20Test%2C%20Was%20Ready%20To%20Play%20Ranji%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndian%20cricket%20team%20batter%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Shubman%20Gill%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F108578-shubman-gill-playerprofile%5C%22%3EShubman%20Gill%3C%2Fa%3E%20gave%20a%20perfect%20reply%20to%20his%20critics%20with%20a%20brilliant%20century%20on%20Day%203%20of%20the%20second%20Test%20match%20against%20England%20in%20Vishakhapatnam%20on%20Sunday.%20Gill%20had%20a%20couple%20of%20cl